    Final check on unary: `parseUnary` is called by `parseTerm`. `parseTerm` is called by `parseExpression`.
    If input is `-5 * 2`:
    `parseExpression` calls `parseTerm`.
    `parseTerm` calls `parseUnary`.
    `parseUnary` sees `-`, calls `parseUnary`.
    `parseUnary` calls `parsePrimary` -> `5`.
    `parseUnary` returns `-5`.
    `parseTerm` sees `*`, calls `parseUnary` -> `2`.
    `parseTerm` returns `-10`.
    `parseExpression` returns `-10`.
